From: Thorch contributors
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: qcom: sm8550: add lowest GPU OPP

The AYN Thor Android device tree exposes 124.8 MHz as the lowest A740
operating point.  It uses the same LOW_SVS_D2 rail level and minimum DDR
bandwidth vote as the 220 MHz operating point.  Add that characterized level
to the mainline SM8550 GPU OPP table so the GMU DCVS table matches the vendor
frequency range.

The GMU adds its separate zero-frequency/off entry when it constructs the HFI
performance table; this node is the lowest running frequency, not the off
state.
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi
@@ -2569,6 +2569,12 @@ gpu_opp_table: opp-table {
 					opp-peak-kBps = <2136718>;
 					qcom,opp-acd-level = <0xc02f5ffd>;
 				};
+
+				opp-124800000 {
+					opp-hz = /bits/ 64 <124800000>;
+					opp-level = <RPMH_REGULATOR_LEVEL_LOW_SVS_D2>;
+					opp-peak-kBps = <2136718>;
+				};
 			};
 		};

